        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_cænk0yl" xml:lang="os-x-iron">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>cænk˳yl</orth></form>
                <usg><lang/></usg>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>безрукий</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>armless</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сухорукий</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>having a withered arm</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Gosæzijæn jæ kæstær fyrt Mixel cænk˳yl wyd</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>младший сын Госази, Михел, был сухорукий</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Gosæzi's younger son, Mikhel, had a withered arm</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>fælæ k˳yvd k˳y kænys, wæd ærxon mæg˳yrgūrty, cænk˳ylty, kʼ˳ylyxty,
                            k˳yrmyty</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>но когда делаешь пир, зови нищих, увечных, хромых, слепых</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>but when thou makest a feast, call the poor, the maimed, the lame,
                                the blind</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Лука"/><biblScope>%i14%i
                            13</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Из <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cong"/> ‘рука’ и %ik˳yl%i;
                    элемент %ik˳yl%i, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_k0yr-"/> участвует в ряде слов,
                    обозначающих физические недостатки: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_k0yræfcæg"/>
                    ‘короткошеий’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼ0ylyx"/> ‘хромой’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_k0yrm"/> ‘слепой’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼ0yrma"/>
                    ‘глухой’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼ0yllaw"/> ‘больной грыжей’; сближается
                    с элементом <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>-кур</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w>-кар</w></mentioned> в
                    таких %bрусских%b словосложениях, как <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>курносый</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                        ><w>корноухий</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                        ><w>карзубый</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                        ><w>кургузый</w></mentioned> (см.: <bibl><author>Фрейман</author><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_ДАН"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1924, стр.
                            49</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1924, p. 49</biblScope></bibl>).
                    Об „инверсии“ (%icæng-k˳yl%i вместо %ik˳yl-cong%i) см. <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>231—236</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">From <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cong"/> ‘hand’ and %ik˳yl%i;
                    the element %ik˳yl%i, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_k0yr-"/> is found in a
                    number of words meaning physical impairment: <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_k0yræfcæg"/> ‘short-necked’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_kʼ0ylyx"/> ‘limping’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_k0yrm"/>
                    ‘blind’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼ0yrma"/> ‘deaf’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_kʼ0yllaw"/> ‘one who has rupture’; it is close to the element
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>-kur</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w>-kar</w></mentioned> in
                    such %bRussian%b compounds as <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>kurnosyj</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                        ><w>kornouxij</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                        ><w>karzubyj</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                        ><w>kurguzyj</w></mentioned> (see: <bibl><author>Фрейман</author><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_ДАН"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1924, стр.
                            49</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1924, p. 49</biblScope></bibl>).
                    As fot the “inversion” (%icæng-k˳yl%i instead of %ik˳yl-cong%i) see <bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                    /><biblScope>231—236</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
